codex
Implemented the PHP classifieds app with SQLite storage.

Created:
- `composer.json` with PHP/PDO SQLite requirements and `composer start`
- `README.md` with local run instructions for port `5040`
- `public/index.php` router/controller
- `src/bootstrap.php` database setup, auth helpers, upload handling
- `views/...` templates for browsing, auth, dashboard, listing CRUD, errors
- `public/styles.css` for the UI

The app supports registration/login, posting listings with photos, category filtering, search, listing details, and seller-only edit/delete. I did not run or test it because the workspace instructions explicitly say to only write source files.
diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..ab02356d603dd5e2f29695b78d878a2e9512dbe6
--- /dev/null
+++ b/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,24 @@
+# PHP Classifieds
+
+A lightweight classifieds site where visitors can browse listings by category and search, while logged-in sellers can post, edit, and delete their own items.
+
+## Requirements
+
+- PHP 8.1 or newer
+- PDO SQLite extension enabled
+- Composer
+
+## Run locally on port 5040
+
+```bash
+composer install
+composer start
+```
+
+Then open:
+
+```text
+http://127.0.0.1:5040
+```
+
+The app creates its SQLite database automatically at `database/classifieds.sqlite` on first run.
